author: David K. Li
title: 1 million in California file for unemployment as state feels economic hit of coronavirus
description: California feeling the economic hit, 1 million unemployment claims in the Golden State.
content:
One million Californians filed unemployment claims this month, as America's most populous state braces for an economic blow from the coronavirus pandemic, officials said Wednesday.
